1 & CPT alone\\
2 & SFT + Synthetic Data\\
3 & Reasoning Distillation\\
4 & RL Methods (DPO/PPO)\\
5 & Model Merging\\
6 & Pruning/Sparsification\\
7 & Extreme Quantization\\
8 & Test-Time Compute\\
9 & Pre-train from Scratch\\
10 & \textbf{Full Pipeline} $\bigstar$\\
\end{tabular}
\end{block}

\column{0.33\textwidth}
\begin{block}{10 Evaluation Criteria}
\scriptsize
\begin{tabular}{@{}l@{}}
Knowledge Retention\\
Inference Cost (mobile)\\
Training Cost\\
Data Efficiency\\
Domain QA Accuracy\\
Mobile Deployability\\
Robustness\\
Catastrophic Forgetting\\
Maintenance Burden\\
Proven at Small Scale\\
\end{tabular}
\end{block}

\column{0.31\textwidth}
\begin{block}{21 Research Documents}
\scriptsize
\begin{tabular}{@{}ll@{}}
Token corpus: & 42.75M\\
arXiv papers: & 17+\\
Ranking docs: & 10 MD\\
Deep-dive docs: & 5 MD\\
Dataset docs: & 4 MD\\
Planning docs: & 2 MD\\
\end{tabular}
\end{block}

\vspace{4pt}
\begin{successblock}{Key Insight}
\scriptsize No single approach wins. Which \textbf{combination}, in what sequence, gives the best accuracy-to-cost ratio?
\end{successblock}
\end{columns}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{Dataset: 42.75 Million Maritime Tokens}
\begin{columns}[T]
\column{0.50\textwidth}
\begin{block}{Corpus Statistics}
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{@{}lr@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Component} & \textbf{Size}\\
\midrule
JSONL Articles (38,840 files) & 14.24M tokens\\
Extracted .txt (4,334 files) & 17.83M tokens\\
Scraped web data & $\sim$10.68M tokens\\
\midrule
\textbf{TOTAL CORPUS} & \textbf{42.76M tokens}\\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}
\end{block}

\begin{block}{20+ Data Sources}
\scriptsize
IMO, MAIB, NTSB, MCA, EMSA, USCG, Gard P\&I, UK P\&I, NEPIA, DNV, ClassNK, Lloyd's Register, ABS, OCIMF, BIMCO, Wartsila, Safety4Sea, gCaptain, MarineInsight, Hellenic Shipping News, Wikipedia Maritime
\end{block}

\column{0.47\textwidth}
\begin{successblock}{Token Scaling Assessment}
\scriptsize
\textbf{Chinchilla Law} (Hoffmann 2022): optimal full pretrain = \textbf{20 tokens/param}\\
For Qwen3-4B: $20 \times 4\text{B} = 80$B tokens optimal (full pretraining scale)\\[2pt]
\textbf{AdaptLLM} (arXiv:2309.09530) --- domain CPT on LLaMA-7B:
\begin{itemize}
  \item Finance corpus: \textbf{1.2B tokens} (171M tok/B-param)
  \item BioMed corpus: \textbf{5.4B tokens} (771M tok/B-param)
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Our ratio:} $42.75$M $\div$ 4B params = \textbf{10.7M tok/B-param}\\
\textbf{Verdict:} Strong v1 foundation; target \textbf{200M+ tokens} for optimal CPT.\\[2pt]
\textbf{3 Knowledge Types:} Procedural $\cdot$ Theoretical $\cdot$ Incident/Case studies
\end{successblock}

\begin{warningblock}{Current: Dataset Health 4.5/10 $\to$ Plan: 10/10}
\scriptsize
Textbook-heavy, \textbf{procedure-light}. Missing: cargo ops (tanker/bulk/container), auxiliary machinery (OWS, FWG), GMDSS, ECDIS. OWS is \#1 PSC detention item.\\
\textbf{3-week, \$350 remediation plan} targets 67M tokens $\to$ \textbf{10/10 health} (see dedicated slide).
\end{warningblock}
\end{columns}
\end{frame}

