\begin{successblock}{Setup: Zero IT Department}
\scriptsize
\textbf{In port (once):} \texttt{ollama pull qwen3:4b}\\
\textbf{Simplest:} llamafile --- single \texttt{.exe}, model bundled, double-click.\\
\textbf{At sea:} Fully offline, no configuration.
\end{successblock}
\end{columns}
\end{frame}

% ============================================================
\section{Honest Limitations}
% ============================================================

\begin{frame}{Honest Limitations: What This Model Cannot Do}
\begin{columns}[T]
\column{0.48\textwidth}
\begin{dangerblock}{Hard Technical Limitations}
\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Exact numbers} $\approx$ 60--75\% accuracy --- MARPOL discharge limits, exact ppm values: verify in official docs
  \item \textbf{Q4 quantization} loses 1--3\% vs fp16
  \item \textbf{No real-time updates} --- model is static until retrained
  \item \textbf{Hallucinations persist} on rare/obscure regulations
  \item \textbf{Mathematical precision weak} --- voyage calculations need verification
  \item \textbf{Cargo ops} largely uncovered in v1 dataset
  \item \textbf{Not validated} on STCW exam format
\end{itemize}
\end{dangerblock}

\column{0.48\textwidth}
\begin{warningblock}{Maintenance Commitment Required}
\scriptsize
\textbf{IMO adopts $\sim$3--5 amendments/year.}\\
\textbf{MARPOL amendments:} $\sim$2--3/year.\\
\textbf{Quarterly retraining cycle needed.}\\[4pt]
Each update:
\begin{enumerate}
  \item Gather new data (circulars, amendments)
  \item Run CPT on delta updates
  \item Regenerate affected Q\&A pairs
  \item Re-run SFT, re-DPO
  \item Re-merge, re-quantize, re-deploy
\end{enumerate}
\textbf{Per-update cost:} \$40--150.\\
\textbf{Per-update time:} 1--3 days.
\end{warningblock}
\end{columns}

\vspace{6pt}
\begin{goldblock}{$\bigstar$ Correct Positioning for Ships}
\begin{center}
\large\bfseries Maritime Study Aid \& Quick Reference Tool\\[2pt]
\normalsize NOT a regulatory compliance tool. NOT a safety-critical decision system.\\
\small\normalfont Excellent for: learning, exam prep, watch routine Q\&A, troubleshooting guidance.\\
Always verify critical information against official IMO publications and class society rules.
\end{center}
\end{goldblock}
\end{frame}

% ============================================================
\section{Roadmap \& Key Papers}
% ============================================================

\begin{frame}{4-Week Execution Roadmap}
\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.90]
  \tikzstyle{wk}=[draw, rounded corners=4pt, minimum height=0.65cm, minimum width=2.8cm, align=center, font=\footnotesize\bfseries]

  \node[wk, fill=lightblue!60, draw=maritime] (w1) at (0,0) {Week 1};
  \node[right, font=\footnotesize, text width=10.0cm] at (1.5,0) {Data prep: clean \& tokenize corpus, generate 20K--50K Q\&A pairs via GPT-4o or Qwen3-32B, apply 2 rounds Evol-Instruct, DEITA-style quality filtering to 6K--20K best samples.};

  \node[wk, fill=lightgreen!60, draw=darkgreen] (w2) at (0,-1.0) {Week 2};
  \node[right, font=\footnotesize, text width=10.0cm] at (1.5,-1.0) {CPT training: QLoRA r=32 on Qwen3-4B, 2--3 epochs on 42.75M token corpus. Use Unsloth for 2$\times$ speedup. Run on T4 (\$10--20) or A100 (\$30--50) GPU instance.};

  \node[wk, fill=lightyellow!80, draw=warning] (w3) at (0,-2.0) {Week 3};
  \node[right, font=\footnotesize, text width=10.0cm] at (1.5,-2.0) {SFT: train on Q\&A pairs with NEFTune enabled, evaluate on held-out maritime set. DPO: generate 1K--5K preference pairs, align with safety refusals, $\beta$=0.01.};

  \node[wk, fill=gold!35, draw=gold!80] (w4) at (0,-3.0) {Week 4};
  \node[right, font=\footnotesize, text width=10.0cm] at (1.5,-3.0) {Model soup: MergeKit 0.9$\times$DPO + 0.1$\times$pre-DPO. Quantize to Q4\_K\_M GGUF via llama.cpp. Deploy with Ollama. Evaluate on final maritime QA benchmark.};

  \draw[thick, maritime!40] (-1.5,-3.65) -- (11.5,-3.65);
  \node[font=\small\bfseries, text=maritime] at (5.0,-4.1) {Total: \textbf{\$40--400} \quad|\quad \textbf{4 weeks} elapsed time \quad|\quad \textbf{1--2 engineers} needed};
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{Key Research Papers Underpinning Every Decision}
\begin{center}
\scriptsize
\begin{tabular}{@{}p{5.5cm}p{6.5cm}l@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Paper} & \textbf{Key Finding Used} & \textbf{arXiv}\\
\midrule
Phi-1 ``Textbooks Are All You Need'' & Synthetic textbook data beats 10$\times$ data volume & 2306.11644\\
QLoRA (Dettmers et al.) & 4-bit base + fp16 LoRA $\approx$ full FT quality & 2305.14314\\
LoRA Learns Less and Forgets Less & r=64 absorbs 88\% of Full FT; target MLP layers & 2405.09673\\
DPO (Direct Preference Optimization) & Alignment without RL, $\beta$=0.01 optimal & 2305.18290\\
Smaug/DPOP & DPO can reduce preferred likelihood --- use KTO & 2402.13228\\
AdaptLLM & Domain CPT on LLaMA-7B (1.2B--16.7B tok corpora); reading-comprehension method & 2309.09530\\
NEFTune & Noise in embeddings: +35\% accuracy, zero compute & 2310.05914\\
DEITA & 6K curated = 60K+ generic training samples & 2312.15685\\
Don't Stop Pretraining & Domain CPT consistently beneficial for specialization & 2004.10964\\
GaLore & Full-rank updates with LoRA memory budget & 2403.07691\\
LAB (taxonomy-guided synthetic data) & Structured taxonomy ensures domain coverage & 2403.01081\\
DeepSeek-R1 Technical Report & Distillation to 1.5B works; RL at $\leq$3B: use distillation & 2501.12948\\
SmolLM3 (HuggingFace Blog 2025) & Full open 3B pipeline proof-of-concept & Blog 2025\\
ROME (Meng et al., NeurIPS 2022) & Facts in MLP layers 15--25 (middle transformer layers) & NeurIPS 22\\
Qwen3 Technical Report & Architecture, 36T token training, think/no-think mode & 2505.09388\\
s1: 32B test-time scaling & Myth debunked: uses 32B model not 1B & 2501.19393\\
BioMedLM (2.7B, PubMed 2024) & Best from-scratch analogue; 69\% MMLU Medical & 2403.18421\\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}
\end{frame}

% ============================================================
\section{Conclusion}
% ============================================================

\begin{frame}{Final Decision: The Evidence-Based Choice}
\begin{center}
\begin{goldblock}{$\bigstar$ The Winning Approach --- 73/100}
\large\centering\bfseries
CPT (42.75M tokens) $+$ Synthetic SFT (20K--50K Q\&A) $+$ DPO Alignment\\
$+$ Model Soup $+$ Q4\_K\_M GGUF $\to$ \textbf{Offline Ship AI Chatbot}
\end{goldblock}
\end{center}

\vspace{6pt}
\begin{columns}[T]
\column{0.31\textwidth}
\begin{successblock}{Why This Wins}
\scriptsize
\begin{itemize}
  \item Only pipeline combining knowledge injection AND instruction-following
  \item Proven: SmolLM3 (3B), Phi-1 (1.3B), Orca 2 (7B)
  \item \$40--400 total build cost
  \item 1--2 day cloud GPU time
  \item Fully offline deployment
  \item 100+ language support
\end{itemize}
\end{successblock}
\column{0.31\textwidth}
\begin{block}{What We Achieve}
\scriptsize
\begin{itemize}
  \item 65--75\% accuracy on maritime QA
  \item Runs on any laptop (CPU-only)
  \item 5--25 tok/s response speed
  \item 2.5--4.5 GB RAM (Qwen3-4B Q4)
  \item Zero internet at inference time
  \item Quarterly update cycle possible
\end{itemize}
\end{block}
\column{0.31\textwidth}
\begin{warningblock}{Accepted Tradeoffs}
\scriptsize
\begin{itemize}
  \item Study aid, NOT compliance tool
  \item Exact numbers: 35--55\% reliable
  \item Cargo ops undercovered in v1
  \item Static knowledge, no live updates
  \item Quarterly retraining needed
\end{itemize}
\vspace{4pt}
\textbf{Positioned as:}\\
Maritime Study Aid\\ \& Quick Reference Tool
\end{warningblock}
\end{columns}
\end{frame}

